# .understandignore — patterns for files/dirs to exclude from analysis
# Syntax: same as .gitignore (globs, # comments, ! negation, trailing / for dirs)
# Lines below are suggestions — uncomment to activate.
# Use ! prefix to force-include something excluded by defaults.
#
# Built-in defaults (always excluded unless negated):
#   node_modules/, .git/, dist/, build/, obj/, *.lock, *.min.js, etc.
#

# --- User overrides (highest priority) ---
# The vendored copilot-api is patched by this repo, so its sources are part of
# the project: cancel the built-in "vendor/" exclusion. Its generated bundle
# (dist/) and lockfiles stay excluded via the built-in defaults.
!vendor/
!llm_cli/vendor/
!llm_cli/vendor/copilot-api/src/
!llm_cli/vendor/copilot-api/tests/

# --- From .gitignore (uncomment to exclude) ---

# CLAUDE.md
# AGENTS.md
# RTK.md
# .github/copilot-instructions.md
# .claude/
# .claudeignore
# .copilotignore
# .env
# .mcp.json
# *.bak
# .tokensave/
# *.egg-info/
# !llm_cli/vendor/copilot-api/dist/
# !llm_cli/vendor/copilot-api/dist/**

